Each sprint is 60 meters long.
So, the total meters he runs a week is 9 sprints/week * 60 meters/sprint = 540 meters/week.

Step 1: Calculate the total number of sprints James runs in a week.
James runs 3 sprints per day, 3 times a week.
Total sprints per week = (sprints per day) × (days per week)
